comments: DeRozan (CHI) establishes himself in Allen's (MIL) path and marginal contact occurs as Allen goes under the pick.
Carter (MIL) legally contests LaVine's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
Lopez (MIL) establishes himself in Caruso's (CHI) path and marginal contact occurs as the players engage after the pick is set.
Vucevic (CHI) legally contests Antetokounmpo's (MIL) jump shot attempt.
Caruso (CHI) establishes himself in Holiday's (MIL) path and marginal contact occurs when Holiday goes over the pick.
Caruso (CHI) loses his balance and falls to the floor when incidental foot to foot contact occurs with his teammate, DeRozan (CHI).
Lopez (MIL) is in the lane for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Lopez (MIL) gets to ball height and dislodges the ball during DeRozan's (CHI) driving shot attempt. The contact after the dislodge is considered incidental.
DeRozan (CHI) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Lopez (MIL) extends his arms out slightly as he establishes himself in Caruso's (CHI) path and marginal contact occurs when Caruso goes under the pick.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) gathers the ball and goes through Caruso (CHI), who is established in a legal defensive position, and dislodges him.
Holiday (MIL) absorbs the marginal contact with DeRozan (CHI) during the post backdown.
Holiday (MIL) legally contests White's (CHI) perimeter shot attempt.
DeRozan's (CHI) right arm comes out when he engages with Antetokounmpo (MIL) and the contact during the inbounds pass is marginal.
Connaughton (MIL) firms up in Caruso's (CHI) path and marginal contact occurs as the players come together during the screen.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Holiday's (MIL) pass goes out of bounds and is not deflected by either a teammate or an opponent. Possession is properly awarded to Chicago.
Vucevic (CHI) gives a step of distance when establishing himself in Holiday's (MIL) path and marginal contact occurs during the back-screen.
DeRozan (CHI) engages with Holiday (MIL) as the screen is set and the contact is marginal.
Holiday (MIL) and DeRozan (CHI) come together at the start of DeRozan's drive and the contact is marginal.
Lopez (MIL) legally contests Vucevic's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
Holiday (MIL) briefly loses control of the ball and immediately recovers it. The contact with Caruso (CHI) after the recovery of the ball is marginal.
Vucevic (CHI) lowers his right arm down slightly, and the contact with Antetokounmpo's (MIL) right shoulder is marginal.
Carter (MIL) momentarily places his left hand on DeRozan's (CHI) side and the contact during the inbounds pass is marginal.
Carter (MIL) reaches in for the ball and makes contact with DeRozan's (CHI) body that affects his balance while in possession of the ball.
White (CHI) loses his balance and stumbles towards Connaughton (MIL). The contact with Connaughton, prior to falling to to the ground, is incidental.
DeRozan (CHI) establishes himself in Carter's (MIL) path and marginal contact occurs as the players come together during the inbounds play.
Carter (MIL) commits a take foul on DeRozan (CHI).
Caruso (CHI) moves alongside Antetokounmpo's (MIL) path and the contact during the driving shot attempt is marginal.
Allen (MIL) commits a take foul on Williams (CHI). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
